objects.title: Strandberg Guitars
objects.content:
Tone Temple are exclusive retailers of Strandberg Guitars in Australia and New Zealand. If you are wishing to try or buy a Strandberg guitar and you are in Australia or New Zealand please send us a message at sales@tonetemple.com.au.

.strandberg* Guitars have been evolving for almost a decade with their innovative EndurNeck™, distinctive, ergonomic body shape and headless design and fan frets. The headless design ensures that the guitar is well balanced and lightweight. The patent pending EndurNeck™ promotes better playing position resulting in less fatigue and less risk of injury. In addition to the EndurNeck™ Strandberg Guitars  are designed as multi-scale instruments, the fanned frets allow your wrist to remain relaxed throughout the range of play. The extra length on the bass side enhances sustain, and the shorter treble side makes bends easier.

The .strandberg* Boden body shape provides multiple seated playing positions for maximum comfort and versatility, to suit any playing style. Aircraft grade aluminium and carbon fiber materials are used to maintain a low weight and high performance. The proprietary custom made Strandberg hardware are also made from the highest performance materials to eliminate all potential loss of energy in the strings’ vibration,

The now iconic headless Boden guitar design encompasses 6-, 7-, and 8-string versions that sound, play, and look amazing, for all styles of music. Contact us for more info.

metadata.meta_description: Combining excellent ergonomics with style and aesthetics, the Strandberg Boden is a versatile guitar that sounds and feels as good as it looks. Tone Temple is the exclusive retailer Strandberg Guitars Australia and New Zealand.

objects.title: Friedman Amplification
objects.content:
Dave Friedman is the man behind the signature tones of rock icons Eddie Van Halen, Steve Stevens and Jerry Cantrell. Dave has been building, modding and repairing amplifiers for many of the world’s biggest stars for the past 25 years. Friedman’s innovative designs and meticulous construction have made him legendary in the world of professional touring musicians.

Dave Friedman’s extensive knowledge and pursuit of tonal superiority inspired him to develop his own series of production amplifiers under the name Friedman Amplification. Each Friedman amplifier is built in the U.S.A. to Dave's exacting standards using hand selected components. After a rigorous burn in process, Dave inspects, tubes, plays and signs the chase of every amplifier before shipping them to us.

At Tone Temple we are big fans of the Friedman BE-100, an amp that is one of the most talked about designs for the past few years and our benchmark amplifier. We are also very excited about the new Runt 20 which has an internal load and cab-simulated XLR output, perfect for recording silently at home. However if you would like to purchase any of the Friedman range please contact us at sales@tonetemple.com.au.

metadata.meta_description: Friedman Amplifiers are the new benchmark in guitar amplification. Contact Tone Temple to order your Friedman Amplifiers Australia.

objects.title: Evil Angel Pickups
objects.content:
3 years of intensive research and development in conjunction with Cilia Guitars, Evil Angel Trinity and Trinity+ pickups are finally available to the public. This pickups are very organic sounding and enhance the natural tone of your guitar rather than boosting or scooping frequencies. Charles Cilia has been using the Trinity humbuckers in the guitars such as the Cilia Halo, Aurora and Belladonna.


Artists currently using Evil Angel pickups include Michael Dolce, Irwin Thomas, Chris Kamzelas and Azaria Byrne.

metadata.meta_description: Evil Angel Trinity and Trinity+ pickups are very organic sounding and enhance the natural tone of your guitar rather than boosting or scooping frequencies. Available from Tone Temple Australia & New Zealand.

objects.title: Yankee
objects.content:
Yankee manufactures the best power supply for your pedals that we've come across, the Yankee PS-M2. This is a professional guitar effects power supply with the ability to power virtually every guitar effect available on the market. It is unquestionably the most electronically advanced power supply. 

Manufactured by experienced specialists, PS-M2 is a combination of professional electronic solution and brilliant design.

Yankee PS-M2 Power Supply features:

  • Assembled in durable aluminium housing, using highest quality material providing safety and durability
  • Can be easily attached to pedalboard with screws
  • Powerfull toroidal transformer
  • Movable power cord socket (see photos)
  • 3 AC outputs (9V, 12V and 14V)
  • 2 DC outputs with regulated voltage (between 6V and 24V)
  • 10 9V DC outputs splited into two separated sections
  • 2 SAG with stepless DV voltage regulation between 1V and 10V
  • Five fully separated sections
  • Can power at the same time effects in send/return loop and before the amplifier
  • USB port and diode lamp
  • Ability to power every guitar effect available on the market
  • One of the most advanced Power Supplies on the market

objects.title: Tronical
objects.content:
The TronicalTune is a revolutionary device for electric and acoustic guitars alike that seamlessly self-tunes your guitar in a matter of seconds, all the while preserving the integrity and tone of your instrument. Suitable for various guitar models (currently over 350) with no modification to the instrument at all.  The system consists of a miniaturized micro-controller and six motorized tuning pegs, which insert onto the back of the headstock replacing the existing machine heads. It allows the user to access up to 36 different tunings at the touch of a button.

The TronicalTune system consists of three main components. First, there’s a set of motorized machine heads called RoboHeads. From the front of the headstock, these look like conventional locking tuners. Second, there’s a rectangular box adorned with LEDs, which contains the battery and the brains of the system. And third, there’s a black plate which sits flush against the back of the headstock, with the machine heads passing through it. 

While the ‘brain’ is common to all Tronical configurations. The weight of the system is no more than a set of locking tuners. The internal Lithium-Polymer battery lasts for up to 300 tunings on just one charge and If the system is switched off you can always tune by hand!

objects.title: Ilitch Electronics
objects.content: At Tone Temple we believe there is no better hum cancelling system for single coil pickups than the Illitch products. Ilitch Chiliachki, a former design engineer for Seymour Duncan, founded Illitch Electronics in 2004 and one year later patented his hum cancelling technology for electric guitar single coil pickups and licensed it to Suhr Guitars. In 2011 both companies went their separate ways and Ilitch Electronics expanded his line of Hum cancelling products to cover the most popular guitar models and single coil pickup combinations. Contact us to find out which system will best suit your guitar.
